# PR Workflow

## Language
All PR content MUST be written in **English**.

## Target repository
PRs MUST target `felipeblassioli/agent-skills`. Always use:
```bash
gh pr create --repo felipeblassioli/agent-skills --base main ...
```
NEVER open PRs against `vercel-labs/agent-skills` or any upstream repo.

## Branch naming
`<type>/<skill-name>-<short-description>` or `<type>/<short-description>`

Examples:
- `feat/import-commit-hygiene`
- `fix/tdd-classicist-tier-matrix`
- `chore/update-registry-schema`

## PR title
Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): description`

Use the skill name as scope when the change is skill-specific.
Use `registry`, `build`, or omit scope for cross-cutting changes.

Examples:
- `feat(tdd-classicist): add regression-fix checklist`
- `fix(registry): correct version drift in metadata`
- `docs: update AGENTS.md with new skill paths`

## PR body

Use the template at `.github/pull_request_template.md`. Key sections:

### What
One-paragraph summary of the change. Lead with intent, not mechanics.

### Skills affected
Table listing every skill touched, the nature of change, and version delta.
Delete this section if no skills are affected.

### Motivation
**Why does this change exist?** This is the most important section.
A reviewer should understand the goal before reading code.

| PR size | Guideline |
|---------|-----------|
| Small / trivial | 1–3 sentences |
| Medium | 1 paragraph + optional context |
| Complex | Up to ~10 lines; reference ADRs or issues |

### Quality checklist
The template includes a checklist derived from the skill standard.
Tick every applicable item before requesting review.

Key checks (from `create-skill-from-refs/references/quality-checklist.md`):
- `skill-registry.json` updated when skills are added/removed/versioned
- `metadata.json` version matches the registry entry
- SKILL.md frontmatter: `name` matches folder, `description` includes WHAT + WHEN
- SKILL.md body under 500 lines
- No empty directories in the skill tree
- No secrets or credentials in content

### Validation
Include actual commands and results. Examples:
```
- `bash scripts/skill-sync.sh --dry-run` → OK
- `bash skills/create-skill-from-refs/scripts/validate-skill.sh skills/<name>` → all pass
```

## What makes a good PR in this repo

### Focused scope
Keep PRs short. Separate skill content changes from registry/script changes
from build tooling changes (see commit conventions in `10-commit-conventions.mdc`).

### Explain intent, not just mechanics
The **Motivation** section answers "why does this change exist?" so the
reviewer understands the goal before reading code. A cryptic title and
empty body is the fastest way to get a PR ignored.

### Validate with the skill standard
For PRs that add or substantially modify a skill, run the validation script:
```bash
bash skills/create-skill-from-refs/scripts/validate-skill.sh skills/<name>
```
Include the output in the Validation section.

### Track follow-ups explicitly
When deferring work, open an issue and reference it in **Additional context**.

## Workflow steps

### 1. Gather context
```bash
git log --oneline main..HEAD
git diff main..HEAD --stat
```

### 2. Draft the body
Fill in the `.github/pull_request_template.md` sections.
For complex PRs, stage the body in `.work/body-pr-<slug>.md` and use `--body-file`.

### 3. Create or update

**Create:**
```bash
gh pr create \
  --title "type(scope): description" \
  --body-file .work/body-pr-<slug>.md \
  --base main
```

**Update existing:**
```bash
gh pr edit <NUMBER> --body-file .work/body-pr-<slug>.md
```

### 4. Add proof comments (optional)
Attach validation evidence as a PR comment:
```bash
gh pr comment <NUMBER> --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
### Validation: skill-sync dry-run
```
<paste output>
```
EOF
)"
```

## When importing skills from other repos
- Use `scripts/skill-import.sh` to ensure consistent structure
- Verify the imported SKILL.md frontmatter is valid
- Add meaningful tags in the registry entry
- Single commit for import + registry update

## Quick reference

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| List open PRs | `gh pr list --base main --state open` |
| View PR body | `gh pr view <N> --json body -q .body` |
| Create PR | `gh pr create --title "..." --body-file .work/body-pr-<slug>.md` |
| Update PR body | `gh pr edit <N> --body-file .work/body-pr-<slug>.md` |
| Add comment | `gh pr comment <N> --body "..."` |
| Check CI status | `gh pr checks <N>` |
| Validate skill | `bash skills/create-skill-from-refs/scripts/validate-skill.sh skills/<name>` |
